column2: Winter kill this past winter. Even perch killed. (Also killed zyrago - mostly bass and sucker)
Heard loon last night- and 5 species of frog and toad.
lake slightly cloudy from recent rain and pollen loading.
Ice out was 4/9.  Winterkill. 1000's of minnows- white suckers- ~150 perch.  Minnows already starting to break down.
clear- moderate wind.  Water usual brown tinged. Extra hiliday boat traffic.
clear- no wind- no boat traffic on lake
